# TRIP TAILORS — SOLO FOUNDER RISK MITIGATION & ADVISORY PLAN
**Version 1.0 — January 2026**

---

## 1. SOLO FOUNDER RISK — THE PLAN

### The Narrative (For Investors)

> "I'm a solo founder by choice, not by limitation. I built the product, validated the market, and established partnerships that generate 50 million weekly views — all before asking for a single dollar of investment. My first hire is budgeted for Month 3, and I'm actively building an advisory board with travel industry expertise. The company is designed to run as a system, not dependent on any one person."

### Structural Mitigations (Already in the Plan)

| Risk Factor | Mitigation | When |
|-------------|-----------|------|
| Key person dependency | Agent trainer hired (handles day-to-day agent operations) | Month 3 |
| Technical dependency | Outsourced dev team (not one person) | Month 1 |
| Legal dependency | Outsourced legal counsel | Month 2 |
| Financial dependency | Outsourced accountant | Month 1 |
| Strategic dependency | Advisory board (2-3 advisors) | Month 1-3 |
| Operational documentation | All processes documented in Operational Blueprint | Ongoing |
| Founder burnout | Structured weekly routine, clear delegation, realistic timeline | Ongoing |

### What This Means in Practice
By Month 4 (when agents start joining), the founder is NOT the only person in the business:
- Agent trainer handles agent queries, onboarding calls, training content
- Developer handles platform issues, bug fixes, feature development
- Accountant handles finances, tax compliance, payouts
- Legal counsel handles contract questions
- Advisors provide strategic guidance

**The founder focuses on:** Strategy, agent recruitment (sales), referrer relationships, product direction, and investor relations.

