### Equity Compensation for Advisors

**Standard advisory equity (pre-seed stage):**

| Commitment Level | Equity | Vesting | What They Do |
|-----------------|--------|---------|-------------|
| **Light** (1 call/month, intros when asked) | 0.25% | 2 years, quarterly vesting | Answer questions, make introductions |
| **Standard** (2 calls/month, active intros, event attendance) | 0.5% | 2 years, quarterly vesting | Strategic guidance, investor intros, industry connections |
| **Heavy** (weekly involvement, board observer, hands-on mentoring) | 0.75-1.0% | 2 years, quarterly vesting | Deep involvement, almost co-founder level guidance |

**For Trip Tailors, recommend:**
- 2 advisors at 0.5% each = 1.0% total
- 1 advisor at 0.25% (lighter commitment) = 0.25% total
- **Total advisory equity: 1.25%**
- All with 2-year vesting, quarterly (so if an advisor disengages, unvested equity returns)

**Cap table impact:**
- Founder: 98.75% (pre-investment)
- Advisors: 1.25% (pre-investment)
- Post $310K SAFE at $2.5M cap: Founder ~86.5%, Advisors ~1.1%, Investors ~12.4%

### Advisory Agreement (Simple)

| Clause | Standard Terms |
|--------|---------------|
| Role | Advisory (non-executive, non-binding) |
| Commitment | [X] calls per month, [Y] introductions per quarter |
| Equity | [X]% of fully diluted shares |
| Vesting | 24 months, quarterly, 3-month cliff |
| Expenses | Reimbursed if pre-approved |
| Confidentiality | Standard NDA provisions |
| Termination | Either party, 30 days notice. Vested equity retained. |
| No fiduciary duty | Advisor is not a director and has no fiduciary obligations |

